    rationale: "In structural mechanics, when a force is applied to a continuous structure, stress distributes throughout. However, at a discontinuity (fracture), stress concentrates at that point because the structural integrity is lost. This is why AP compression of the thorax causes pain at the fracture site \u2014 the applied force is transmitted through the rib arc and amplified at the break. Referred pain (A) is a neurological phenomenon, not the primary mechanism here. Intrathoracic pressure changes (C) are minimal with gentle compression. Vascular permeability (D) is not the mechanism.",
